// ============================================================
// HTF DATA — TWO SEPARATE SECURITY CALLS TO PREVENT FLASH
// ============================================================
// FIX: The ghost-candle flash on settings change happens because
// TradingView re-executes the script mid-recalculation and a
// single lookahead_off call briefly returns na for closed bars.
//
// Solution: fetch index 0 (live/current HTF candle) with
// lookahead_off (correct — it is still open), and fetch indices
// 1-19 (all confirmed closed HTF candles) with lookahead_on.
// Closed historical bars fetched with lookahead_on are pinned to
// confirmed OHLC data and NEVER go na during recalculation,
// eliminating the intermediate draw-clear-redraw flash entirely.
// ============================================================

// Call 1: live/current HTF candle only — lookahead_off is correct here
// Build the live HTF candle from chart bars so a settings
// recalculation and the next realtime update produce the same OHLC.
